15 WHEREAS, the center's nationally recognized early intervention model has proven to be
16 successful in curbing unemployment and lowering the rate at which girls return to the
17 juvenile justice system; and
18 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this extraordinary organization be
19 appropriately honored during this special time.
20 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
21 recognize February 26, 2025, as Pace Day at the Capitol in honor of the Pace Center for
22 Girls' years of service on behalf of women and girls in need.
23 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
24 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the Pace Center
25 for Girls.
